4739

of packets transmitted in a cycle by a node depends on packet arrival rate λ and the size of its queue, Q. In a cycle, the number of packets that can arrive to a node is λ · T , while the maximum number of packets that can enter into a node is Q. From the DTMC analysis, η is calculated by,

Q

η = i · πi ,

