F. Performance Analysis When Channel Is Not Error-Free
Packet error rate (PER) is an important performance parameter representing the ratio between the number of failed transmissions and the total number of transmissions. Generally, interference, noise and channel fading are the

4740

IEEE SENSORS JOURNAL, VOL. 18, NO. 11, JUNE 1, 2018

predominant factors that cause errors during packet trans-

missions. These factors can be characterized by signal-to-

noise ratio or signal-to-interference-noise ratio. While many

prior studies concentrated on bit error rate (BER) [25]–[27],

some recent papers have also considered packet or frame error

rate [28]–[30].

